PMID== 8862019
TI  == growth inhibition of a human oral bacterium porphyromonas gingivalis by rat cysteine proteinase inhibitor cystatin s.
AB  == agar diffusion analysis demonstrated that rat cystatin s, a cysteine proteinase inhibitor, inhibited the growth of all tested strains of a human oral, gram-negative anaerobic periodontopathogen porphyromonas gingivalis. its specific inhibitory activity against this tissue-invasive bacterium but not against other  tested oral bacterial species emphasized the importance of specific cysteine proteinases for growth of p. gingivalis.
